<br>
However, the BAH has a higher Damage Bonus (due to higher delay), so will <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> generally</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> do more damage... especially against higher AC mobs.<br>
<br>
The lifetap proc on the BAH, while not to be relied upon, can help alot... especially in longer fights.<br>
<br>
Both have the same or better ratios than the Edge of Honor, and at 51 your Damage Bonus on 2h weapons makes them many times more valuable than 1h weapons... to a class that doesn't have dual weild. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usanthebmoonstare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Santheb Moonstare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/31/02 7:50:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1367.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Black Acrylia Halberd vs. Savage Stone Axe</span><hr size=1> I'd probably go with the SSA.  Just my opinion. <p>Santheb Moonstare--53rd level Cavalier of Rodcet Nife.
